			</text>
			<text id="text01" x="340" y="50" width="355" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">Children engage in a number of activities that indicate that they are trying to understand and participate in reading. These children:&lt;LI&gt;Act out the role of the reader&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Include books and pretend reading in their play&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Begin to "read" their favorite books by themselves, focusing mostly on the pictures&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Tell the story of a book as they flip from picture to picture using language that sounds like reading&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
			</text>
