			<text id="header" x="340" y="20" width="343" height="" autosize="H" style="TITLE" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;FONT SIZE="18"&gt;Emergent Readers&lt;/FONT&gt;</content>
			</text>
			<text id="text01" x="340" y="50" width="351" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Emergent readers demonstrate a knowledge of the alphabet, the concept of what a word is, listening and retelling skills, and verbal expression.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;As a child's literacy knowledge develops, you'll notice that the child will:&lt;/P&gt;&lt;LI&gt;"Read" from books they've heard repeatedly&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Gradually demonstrate the intonation patterns of an adult reader &lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Begin to control early reading strategies such as directionality, word-by-word matching, and concepts of print&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Use pictures to support reading and rely heavily on their knowledge of language&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
			</text>
			<graphic id="ref_icon03" x="575" y="253" width="15" height="15" style="LINK_SWF" visible="true" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="GRAPHIC_HIDE">
