			</text>
			<text id="text01" x="340" y="50" width="356" height="" autosize="H" style="DEFAULT" visible="true" fx="">
				<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Around age 5, children enter school and begin receiving formal literacy instruction. &lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;Most children at the kindergarten level are considered to be emergent readers. They continue to make rapid growth in literacy skills if they are exposed to literacy-rich environments.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;As children's awareness of print develops, they begin to recognize and to read letters and familiar words that they see in books, cereal boxes, signs, and other places in their environments.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
			</text>
